{
  "body" : "Generate a serene poster illustration of {{subjects}}, {{activity}}.\n\n— STYLE (CRITICAL) —\nA clear printmaking / woodcut / linocut / risograph aesthetic. Bold confident outlines drawn with character — slightly hand-drawn weight variation, NOT clinical vector lines. Natural distortion in proportions and forms — figures and objects are slightly stylized, not anatomically rigid. Vintage print feel, like a hand-pulled silkscreen poster from a small independent print studio.\n\n— COLOR —\nStrictly limited palette: {{color_palette}}. Only 2–3 colors total. Each color sits in a flat fill area; no gradients, no airbrush, no photoreal shading. The colors should feel like real screen-printed inks layered on warm paper.\n\n— PRINT TEXTURE —\nVintage print texture throughout the entire image: subtle ink imperfections, tiny ink pinholes, slightly rough edges where ink meets paper. Slight misregistration / offset between color layers — one color shifts a few millimeters off from the outline, exactly as in real risograph or screenprint work. The misregistration is gentle, not chaotic.\n\n— PAPER TEXTURE —\nRough warm paper texture visible across the entire background — natural paper grain, subtle fiber texture, occasional faint speckles, the warmth of recycled or kraft-toned paper. NOT a digital noise filter — it must look like real printed-on-paper.\n\n— COMPOSITION —\nSerene poster composition with generous breathing space. Figures occupy roughly 50–65% of the frame, balanced with large open areas. Background: {{background}}. Props: {{props}}. The viewer's eye rests easily — nothing competes with the figures.\n\n— MOOD —\nQuiet, intimate, contemplative, slow. The kind of poster you'd hang in an independent bookstore, a small café, or a reading nook. It celebrates a small quiet moment, not a dramatic event.\n\n— TYPOGRAPHY —\nIf {{title_text}} is provided, set it in clean editorial sans-serif or refined letterpress style, integrated naturally into the negative space (top, bottom, or side). Subtitle: \"{{subtitle_text}}\" if provided. If both text fields are empty, omit all text — let the illustration breathe alone.\n\n— Capture in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio. —\n\n— Additional details —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid —\n- Do NOT use more than 3 colors\n- Do NOT use gradients, airbrush, or photoreal shading\n- Do NOT use clean vector lines — outlines must have hand-drawn character\n- Do NOT make figures anatomically perfect — embrace gentle natural distortion\n- Do NOT crowd the composition with props or background scenery\n- Do NOT add digital noise filter to fake the texture — it must look like real ink + real paper\n- Do NOT use modern flat illustration style (Behance / dribbble corporate flat)\n- Do NOT use cel-shaded anime, 3D, or photoreal rendering\n- Do NOT add lens flares, glow, sparkles, or any digital embellishments\n- Do NOT add cute stickers, hearts, sparkles, or kawaii decorative motifs\n- Do NOT make the misregistration too aggressive — it must stay refined and intentional\n- Do NOT add extra characters or background figures — keep just the two subjects\n\nKeywords: printmaking, woodcut, linocut, risograph, screenprint poster, hand-pulled print, vintage print texture, paper grain, ink misregistration, limited palette, serene composition, independent bookstore poster, slow living, intimate quiet moment.",
